  <description type="morphology">Trees  to 80m; trunk to 5m diam.; crown narrowly conic.  Bark  grayish brown to orange-brown.  Branches  somewhat drooping; twigs not pendent, rather stout, pinkish brown, glabrous.  Buds  reddish brown, 5--10mm, apex rounded.  Leaves  (1.2--)1.5--2.5(--3)cm, flattened or broadly triangular in cross section (abaxial surface rounded or slightly angular), rather rigid, blue-green to light yellow-green, abaxial surface darker green with stomatal bands very narrow or absent, adaxial surface glaucous with conspicuous stomatal bands separated by ridge, apex sharp-pointed.  Seed cones  5--9(--10)cm; scales variable, elliptic to narrowly diamond-shaped, 15--22 × 12--16mm, rather rigid, margin at apex erose, apex extending 4--8mm beyond seed-wing impression. 2 n =24.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Pacific coastal forests;</description>
  <description type="elevation">0--900m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">B.C.; Alaska, Calif., Oreg., Wash.</description>
